1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:06,030
Today is your lucky day: I got a surprisingly
simple strategy, to finally see some profits

2
00:00:06,030 --> 00:00:08,860
in your account, without taking huge risks.

3
00:00:08,860 --> 00:00:15,150
I’ll split this strategy into 4 different
stages, which are all price action related.

4
00:00:15,150 --> 00:00:19,750
First, you need to find the levels that get
the most attention.

5
00:00:19,750 --> 00:00:24,530
When prices break past support or resistance
levels on a chart, it's called a Break of

6
00:00:24,530 --> 00:00:25,890
Structure.

7
00:00:25,890 --> 00:00:30,320
And this matters a lot, being the first condition
in our strategy.

8
00:00:30,320 --> 00:00:35,280
Break of Structure means the price has moved
significantly past a point where it used to

9
00:00:35,280 --> 00:00:39,510
stop before, going in the same direction as
before.

10
00:00:39,510 --> 00:00:46,250
It's simple: in an uptrend, it's when the
price goes higher than before, and in a downtrend,

11
00:00:46,250 --> 00:00:49,440
it's when the price goes lower than before.

12
00:00:49,440 --> 00:00:54,540
When the market keeps making higher highs
and higher lows, in an uptrend, you pick the

13
00:00:54,540 --> 00:00:56,320
latest high point.

14
00:00:56,320 --> 00:01:01,760
If the price keeps going up and closes above
this point for a while, that's a Break of

15
00:01:01,760 --> 00:01:03,210
Structure.

16
00:01:03,210 --> 00:01:08,979
But when the market's making lower lows and
lower highs in a downtrend, you pick the most

17
00:01:08,979 --> 00:01:10,410
recent low.

18
00:01:10,410 --> 00:01:16,870
If the price keeps dropping and closes below
this low, that's another Break of Structure.

19
00:01:16,870 --> 00:01:20,799
The second condition is the development of
a change of character.

20
00:01:20,799 --> 00:01:26,181
A Change of Character happens when the market
starts to go in the opposite direction, after

21
00:01:26,181 --> 00:01:29,470
breaking its previous highs or lows.

22
00:01:29,470 --> 00:01:34,040
It's like a sudden and big change in how the
price moves in the market.

23
00:01:34,040 --> 00:01:41,000
For instance, we have this market that's been
going down, making lower highs and lower lows.

24
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:47,350
If suddenly the price breaks above its last
major high point, that's a Change of Character.

25
00:01:47,350 --> 00:01:52,469
It suggests the market might be turning around,
with buyers taking over.

26
00:01:52,469 --> 00:01:59,090
If the price keeps going up, making new highs
and lows, we're now in a minor uptrend.

27
00:01:59,090 --> 00:02:05,580
Here, the price has been going up, making
higher highs and higher lows.

28
00:02:05,580 --> 00:02:09,310
Look at the past breaks of structure, going
with the trend.

29
00:02:09,310 --> 00:02:15,640
But then, after one of these breaks of structure,
the price turns around and makes a new lower

30
00:02:15,640 --> 00:02:16,970
low.

31
00:02:16,970 --> 00:02:19,910
This suggests the trend might be changing.

32
00:02:19,910 --> 00:02:26,170
After a small pullback, the price starts making
lower lows and lower highs, showing a new

33
00:02:26,170 --> 00:02:29,280
downward trend might be starting.

34
00:02:29,280 --> 00:02:33,580
. The previous bullish trend has now shifted
into a bearish one.

35
00:02:33,580 --> 00:02:39,709
So, to recap, first condition is a Break of
Structure, which means the market structure

36
00:02:39,709 --> 00:02:42,560
keeps going in the same direction.

37
00:02:42,560 --> 00:02:48,790
The second condition is a Change of Character,
which means price might be changing direction.

38
00:02:48,790 --> 00:02:53,900
After you find these 2 patterns, now I want
you to take the Fibonacci tool, and apply

39
00:02:53,900 --> 00:02:59,870
it from highest point of the break of structure,
to the lowest point of the change of character.

40
00:02:59,870 --> 00:03:05,480
We’re interested in pullbacks to the 50%
- 61.8% Fibonacci area.

41
00:03:05,480 --> 00:03:08,000
That’s the third condition.

42
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:14,340
Price tends to go back about 50% of the distance
after a big move, and even after smaller moves

43
00:03:14,340 --> 00:03:15,340
too.

44
00:03:15,340 --> 00:03:18,220
This happens a lot and you can see it on any
chart.

45
00:03:18,220 --> 00:03:26,090
So, we’ll keep an eye out for pullbacks
to this Fibonacci golden zone, because they

46
00:03:26,090 --> 00:03:31,260
often show a high chance for the price to
bounce back in the direction it was going

47
00:03:31,260 --> 00:03:32,580
before.

48
00:03:32,580 --> 00:03:37,640
The Fibonacci Golden Zone is a go-to gem for
finding great trades.

49
00:03:37,640 --> 00:03:43,190
You’ll often find that prices get zapped
like magnets to this special area.

50
00:03:43,190 --> 00:03:45,439
Big money traders watch these levels too.

51
00:03:45,439 --> 00:03:51,670
It’s common knowledge that major players
like banks use these levels in their trading.

52
00:03:51,670 --> 00:03:55,890
And by lining up with the big dogs, you're
ready to run with the pack.

53
00:03:55,890 --> 00:04:02,250
If they want to buy or sell at the same spot,
it can push the price quite aggressively.

54
00:04:02,250 --> 00:04:07,569
Very important: you might not get an instant
rejection right away, when price reaches the

55
00:04:07,569 --> 00:04:09,069
zone.

56
00:04:09,069 --> 00:04:12,060
Prices need to chill and regroup sometimes.

57
00:04:12,060 --> 00:04:15,140
So consider this area as a memory zone.

58
00:04:15,140 --> 00:04:18,950
If prices bounced there before, they'll likely
bounce again.

59
00:04:18,950 --> 00:04:23,220
It’s a good area to take trades if you missed
it the first time.

60
00:04:23,220 --> 00:04:27,460
Now, it's not enough for the price to just
touch the zone.

61
00:04:27,460 --> 00:04:30,210
We need to see it reject off the level.

62
00:04:30,210 --> 00:04:36,660
The fourth condition is a wick, rejecting
the zone, a long thin line above or below

63
00:04:36,660 --> 00:04:37,789
the candle body.

64
00:04:37,789 --> 00:04:41,479
Wicks show fierce rejection of that level.

65
00:04:41,479 --> 00:04:47,039
When a wick spikes down, for example, but
closes back up, it demonstrates the buyers

66
00:04:47,039 --> 00:04:49,420
have stepped in with force.

67
00:04:49,420 --> 00:04:56,440
Wicks reveal the price "tested the waters"
at the zone before rapidly bouncing back.

68
00:04:56,440 --> 00:05:00,190
Like dipping your toe in the pool before jumping
out.

69
00:05:00,190 --> 00:05:05,830
A long wick into the zone combined with the
other factors screams rejection.

70
00:05:05,830 --> 00:05:11,759
Of course, we need a backup plan, in case
the price goes right through the Golden Zone.

71
00:05:11,759 --> 00:05:18,009
Set your stop-loss just above or below the
78% Fibonacci level.

72
00:05:18,009 --> 00:05:21,419
We're looking at chart that's been in a clear
uptrend, making higher highs and higher lows

73
00:05:21,419 --> 00:05:22,419
over time.

74
00:05:22,419 --> 00:05:26,320
This shows strong buying pressure pushing
the price up overall.

75
00:05:26,320 --> 00:05:32,330
At this point, the price breaks above the
previous high, confirming the uptrend is continuing

76
00:05:32,330 --> 00:05:34,310
with a Break of Structure.

77
00:05:34,310 --> 00:05:40,050
Soon after this, the price starts falling
and makes a new lower low.

78
00:05:40,050 --> 00:05:45,670
This signals a Change of Character, suggesting
the uptrend may be weakening.

79
00:05:45,670 --> 00:05:50,860
We take the Fibonacci tool from the Break
of Structure high down to the Change of Character

80
00:05:50,860 --> 00:05:52,130
low.

81
00:05:52,130 --> 00:05:54,310
This shows us the 50%-61.8% pullback zone.

82
00:05:54,310 --> 00:05:58,880
We want price to pull back right into that
Fibonacci zone.

83
00:05:58,880 --> 00:06:03,320
Which it did, printing a long wick before
closing back down.

84
00:06:03,320 --> 00:06:07,530
This long wick into the zone shows rejection
by sellers.

85
00:06:07,530 --> 00:06:14,220
We have a high probability sell setup, with
a stop above the 78% Fibonacci level and targeting

86
00:06:14,220 --> 00:06:17,000
double the amount we risked.

87
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:23,009
We analyze the Crude Oil market, which was
in a clear downtrend on the 4-hour time frame,

88
00:06:23,009 --> 00:06:29,370
with lower highs and lower lows, showing strong
selling pressure overall.

89
00:06:29,370 --> 00:06:36,250
After a bounce up, the price makes a new lower-low,
breaking market structure to confirm the sellers

90
00:06:36,250 --> 00:06:38,000
remain in control.

91
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:44,580
However, on the next days, the price rockets
up and breaks the previous lower high.

92
00:06:44,580 --> 00:06:49,780
This is a Change of Character, signaling potential
weakness in the downtrend.

93
00:06:49,780 --> 00:06:56,160
We draw our Fibonacci from the lower low of
the break of structure, up to the high created

94
00:06:56,160 --> 00:07:00,440
on the change of character, to find the pullback
area.

95
00:07:00,440 --> 00:07:06,479
We now see that price pulls right back into
that zone, and prints a long wick up before

96
00:07:06,479 --> 00:07:08,290
closing back up.

97
00:07:08,290 --> 00:07:13,300
The wick into the Fibonacci area tells us
buyers are rejecting that zone.

98
00:07:13,300 --> 00:07:20,270
I see it as a great opportunity for a long
setup, with a stop right below the 78% Fibonacci

99
00:07:20,270 --> 00:07:24,370
level and targeting double the amount we risked.

100
00:07:24,370 --> 00:07:25,700
And look what happened.

101
00:07:25,700 --> 00:07:30,379
I don’t know how to call it…bad luck…or
bad stop placement.

102
00:07:30,379 --> 00:07:36,630
The price reached 78% level, broke slightly
below it, stopped me from the trade…and

103
00:07:36,630 --> 00:07:41,760
you guessed it…went straight back up, right
to my take profit area.

104
00:07:41,760 --> 00:07:46,870
Lesson learned: never put the stop loss so
close to the 78% level.

105
00:07:46,870 --> 00:07:51,360
Leave the market some room for stop hunts,
market noise and others.

106
00:07:51,360 --> 00:07:56,120
This would have been a home run, if I had
my stop just a bit lower!

107
00:07:56,120 --> 00:08:01,599
In this chart, the market is in an uptrend,
and you can see a pattern of higher highs

108
00:08:01,599 --> 00:08:03,310
and higher lows.

109
00:08:03,310 --> 00:08:06,909
This is the first sign that buyers are in
control.

110
00:08:06,909 --> 00:08:09,199
Now, first condition.

111
00:08:09,199 --> 00:08:14,840
We're looking at a Break of Structure, with
this recent high that has been surpassed,

112
00:08:14,840 --> 00:08:17,319
and the price has closed above it.

113
00:08:17,319 --> 00:08:21,080
Next, we're on the lookout for a Change of
Character.

114
00:08:21,080 --> 00:08:27,970
After our break of structure, the price takes
a breather and dips down, making a lower low.

115
00:08:27,970 --> 00:08:34,300
With our Fibonacci tool in hand, we draw from
the highest point of our Break of Structure,

116
00:08:34,300 --> 00:08:37,850
down to the lowest point of the Change of
Character.

117
00:08:37,850 --> 00:08:42,940
We're interested in a pullback – we want
the price to come back up to the Fibonacci

118
00:08:42,940 --> 00:08:44,250
golden zone.

119
00:08:44,250 --> 00:08:50,950
When we see this long wick into the zone – combined
with our other conditions, it's our cue.

120
00:08:50,950 --> 00:08:55,769
We're seeing sellers stepping back in and
it's time to make our move.

121
00:08:55,769 --> 00:09:03,339
We enter a short trade, setting our stop-loss
just above the 78% Fibonacci level, to be

122
00:09:03,339 --> 00:09:04,339
safe.

123
00:09:04,339 --> 00:09:07,540
Here the market has been in a clear downtrend.

124
00:09:07,540 --> 00:09:13,600
We see lower lows and lower highs – signs
that the sellers have the upper hand.

125
00:09:13,600 --> 00:09:19,970
As we apply our strategy, we first identify
a Break of Structure to the downside.

126
00:09:19,970 --> 00:09:24,980
There's a recent low that's been broken, and
the price has closed below it.

127
00:09:24,980 --> 00:09:30,329
After that, the price starts to climb, breaking
past the last lower high.

128
00:09:30,329 --> 00:09:33,990
It's a Change of Character, and that’s the
second condition.

129
00:09:33,990 --> 00:09:36,740
The sellers might be losing their grip.

130
00:09:36,740 --> 00:09:42,510
We grab our trusty Fibonacci tool and measure
from the Break of Structure low, to the Change

131
00:09:42,510 --> 00:09:44,480
of Character high.

132
00:09:44,480 --> 00:09:47,450
We're now watching the Fibonacci golden zone.

133
00:09:47,450 --> 00:09:50,730
This is where we expect the price to retrace.

134
00:09:50,730 --> 00:09:56,880
And as predicted, the price declines, with
a wick that pokes up into the zone.

135
00:09:56,880 --> 00:10:00,589
It's a clear sign that the buyers aren't done
yet.

136
00:10:00,589 --> 00:10:03,829
They're pushing back, and we're ready to join
them.

137
00:10:03,829 --> 00:10:10,780
We place our buy trade, setting a stop-loss
just below the 78% Fibonacci level, to cover

138
00:10:10,780 --> 00:10:12,079
our backs.

139
00:10:12,079 --> 00:10:17,170
And we are aiming for a target that's twice
the size of our risk.

140
00:10:17,170 --> 00:10:21,890
Regarding which time frame should you choose,
remember that markets are fractal.

141
00:10:21,890 --> 00:10:28,120
A fractal is a pattern that repeats itself
at different scales, like little mini-versions

142
00:10:28,120 --> 00:10:30,060
of the bigger picture.

143
00:10:30,060 --> 00:10:35,519
Price movements form similar patterns, whether
you're looking at a 1-minute chart or a weekly

144
00:10:35,519 --> 00:10:36,519
chart.

145
00:10:36,519 --> 00:10:38,779
The only difference is the time frame.

146
00:10:38,779 --> 00:10:44,440
No matter the time frame, the principles of
support, resistance, trends and breakouts

147
00:10:44,440 --> 00:10:46,560
apply in similar ways.

148
00:10:46,560 --> 00:10:52,100
We are looking for signs of strength, wait
for a change in the tide, measure our bounce

149
00:10:52,100 --> 00:10:56,649
zone, and demand a clear rejection before
making a move.

150
00:10:56,649 --> 00:11:01,070
This approach will keep you aligned with the
market's momentum, whether you're joining

151
00:11:01,070 --> 00:11:04,519
the buyers or tagging along with the sellers.

152
00:11:04,519 --> 00:11:10,050
The key is knowing which time frame to trade,
based on your style and goals.

153
00:11:10,050 --> 00:11:15,329
I personally use it on higher time frames,
this is where signals are more powerful and

154
00:11:15,329 --> 00:11:16,550
reliable.

155
00:11:16,550 --> 00:11:19,459
And remember, it’s all about probabilities.

156
00:11:19,459 --> 00:11:21,610
You will encounter losing trades.

157
00:11:21,610 --> 00:11:26,200
But by following this strategy, you're stacking
the odds in your favor.

158
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:32,270
You're not guessing; you're using a methodical
approach to pinpoint high-probability trades.

159
00:11:32,270 --> 00:11:38,050
And I may sound like a broken record by now,
but if you also monitor volume, you can filter

160
00:11:38,050 --> 00:11:40,470
the bad signals even more.

161
00:11:40,470 --> 00:11:55,380
These videos will explain how to add the volume
component into your analysis.

